##Wuhan Coffee Shop under the epidemic: Even if the shop collapsed, the Last Cup of coffee to the medical staff

Wechat, boyangcongpeople

The function introduces, peels off the human shell, records the real sensible life. Presented by the in-depth Reporting Department of the Beijing News.

Wakanda coffee, a coffee brand in Wuhan, has just been established more than a year ago. During the outbreak of pneumonia in Wuhan, it became the only coffee shop still operating in the city. Since the third day after Wuhan closed the Han corridor, they have sent 7,850 free "Wuhan Lattes" to frontline medical staff.

The seven Baristas left behind by the WACANDA coffee team, ranging in age from the post-80s to the post-00s, are from Wuhan, Zhengzhou and Iran. Photo courtesy of the respondents

Wen | from the Beijing News, Xie Lei

Editor | Hu Jie proofread | Zhai Yongjun

The text is about 5,510 words long and takes about 11 minutes to read

On February 14, Valentine's Day, front line medical staff at several hospitals in Wuhan received a special gift, a cup of coffee, a rose, and a chocolate. There's a handwritten message on the cup.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On Valentine's Day, the coffee shop received roses from netizens, asking them to help deliver the roses to the medical staff. Photo courtesy of the respondents

This is the 20th day of the Wakanda coffee team delivering free coffee to frontline medical staff. Since the third day after Wuhan closed the Lihan Channel, they have delivered 7,850 Free Wuhan Lattes to frontline medical staff. WAKANDA's team also prepared 520 cups of coffee and chocolates for the special occasion. The rose was sent by a netizen. The note said, because I couldn't buy a mask, I bought a rose and sent it to the angels in White.

Wakanda coffee, a coffee brand in Wuhan, has just been established more than a year ago. During the outbreak of pneumonia in Wuhan, it became the only coffee shop still operating in the city.

The group is made up of seven Baristas from the post-80s generation to the post-00s generation in Wuhan, Zhengzhou and Iran.

As the media coverage grew, the team became widely known, and many netizens liked them on social media. "When you get to Wuhan, the flowers will bloom. You Must Punch in, Wakanda. "

ECHO, one of the two millennials on the team, said, "we don't really think we're so great, so great, we just want to do something cool. "

Some fight to get back, some don't want to leave

On the morning of January 23rd, Tian Yazhen was startled by a news feed on her mobile phone: Wuhan announced that it would close the exit from Han at 10 am today. Major shopping malls, restaurants and entertainment places to suspend business.

Tian Yazhen, a girl born in the 1990s, is the boss of a light coffee drinker in Wakanda, Wuhan. Just two days ago, as the Spring Festival travel rush began, Wakanda coffee shop closed five branches in Wuhan, leaving only Guanggu and Hanjie Open. Most of the out-of-town workers at the seven stores are also heading home.

In fact, at the end of December Tian Yazhen on the "unknown pneumonia" heard, but did not take to heart. "closed city" announcement out, this really realized the seriousness of the matter. After consulting with several partners of the coffee shop, Tian Yazhen decided to close the Han street shop and bring the milk, coffee beans and other materials back to the light valley shop, at least first to save a shop, people stay together also have a rely on each other.

Wakanda Coffee Light Valley shop is located in the World City Light Valley Pedestrian Street, surrounded by major universities, adjacent to the Hubei Provincial Hospital of Traditional Chinese Medicine, Wuhan Third Hospital Light Valley Hospital district and south-central hospital. Student parties, office workers and doctors and nurses make up the majority of consumers, many of whom are heavy coffee consumers. Especially at night, the shop can receive a lot of delivery orders from the hospital.

On the afternoon of Jan. 24, the day after the Han exit was closed, two health care workers in face masks, regular customers, arrived at the cafe. Staff members heard from them that the hospital's workload is now much larger than before suddenly, the epidemic is indeed more serious than expected.

Two doctors with good coffee out of the store, looking at their back, we are some uncomfortable, "medical staff are so hard, but also out to buy coffee in person. "

Tian Yazhen said, that night, a few people in the shop had a small meeting. "We can't just sit at home and do nothing. We've all made our decision to make coffee for the health care workers! "

It's always been the style of this young team. "Who wants to come to Guanggu to make coffee? Send 200 cups of coffee to doctors and nurses in Hubei Provincial Hospital of Traditional Chinese Medicine at noon, " Tian posted in a message on the working group. Unexpectedly, the little friends who stayed in Wuhan signed up one after another, xiao Hao, who is traveling in Chengdu, also said he would like to join. At that time, the epidemic in Wuhan had already begun to break out in a large scale.

Xiao Hao, a native of Wuhan, is the youngest Barista in a group of seven born in the 2000s.

"The kids in Wuhan started to respond. I thought Chengdu is not far from Wuhan, and then they immediately responded. " Everyone advised him not to go back, but Xiao Hao insisted. "At this time, I still want to be with my family and friends. "

So, after five million people left Wuhan one after another, against the crowd, Xiao Hao set foot on the difficult road back home. First his scheduled flight 25 was cancelled because of the pneumonia epidemic, and then when he arrived in Qianjiang on the high-speed train, he found that the high-speed train to Wuhan had also been cancelled. Finally, the family drove from Wuhan to Qianjiang to pick up Xiao Hao. Back and forth after six hours, 26 am, Xiao Hao finally safe return to Wuhan.

Sina, the other Iranian Barista at the coffee shop, also chose to stay in Wuhan with his friends.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Employees focus on preparing coffee. Photo by interviewee

Two years ago, Sina, 27, moved from Iran to the newly opened Wakanda coffee shop because of his love of China. Sina's main job is to make coffee and teach new people to do pull flower, he did pull flower into the shop coffee face the responsibility.

On February 2, Sina received a message from the Iranian embassy that Iran would send a special plane to take Iranian citizens stranded in China back home. Since the outbreak, Sina's family in Iran has been hoping that he would return home as soon as possible, and his friends in the store are urging him to do so.

After some thought, Sina chose to stay in Wuhan.

"foreigners can leave Wuhan and China, but do the Chinese have a chance to leave Wuhan and China? They can't, because this is their home. And this is my second home now. "

"We've seen a lot of superheroes saving humanity in the movies, but in the real world, these doctors and nurses are superheroes, " Sina wrote in a message to his friends, the accompanying photo shows a coffee being delivered to a paramedic.

Five hundred "Wuhan Lattes" are sent to the hospital every day

At 9:30 a.m. on January 26, Tian Yazhen and three baristas arrived at the coffee shop on time.

The quantity was communicated to the hospital one day in advance, and five hundred cups of coffee were delivered in two batches in the morning and afternoon. One of the hospital's regular customers saw Tian Yazhen in the circle of friends said he wanted to send coffee for the medical staff free of charge. He volunteered to help contact the hospital. The other said it would be a very happy thing if he could drink the coffee they made. Everyone was very excited when they received the reply. "There are times when doing charity work is not something you just want to do, but it's something you have to see if there is a need to do it, " Echo  said. "otherwise, doing bad things with good intentions can be stressful for hospitals. ".

Five hundred cups a day is about the same as usual, but the doctors only have lunch and dinner breaks, so they have to get the coffee to the hospital within those two breaks. It was also a test for the Wakanda coffee team.

Grinding beans, pressing powder, extracting, milking, packaging and distribution, Wakanda's staff automatically formed an assembly line. Use the same manufacturing process as usual, Save time-consuming pull flower link, others remain unchanged.

The 300 cups of coffee approved in the morning should be ready in an hour and a half. Time is of the essence, but speed as well as quality must be ensured. To this end, Tian Yazhen before doing a lot of careful homework. For example, the reason why lattes are preferred over American coffee is that American coffee, in addition to being a pick me up, is also a diuretic, making it extremely inconvenient for health care workers who have to work for hours in isolation suits. In addition, the usual temperature of making lattes between 55 °c-65 °C, taste and nutrition is the best. But now they keep the milk at around 80 °C to make sure the coffee is still warm when it reaches the hands of health care workers.

After the coffee is made, Echo and Duan will drive to the hospital before 12 o'clock.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Echo and Duan are responsible for the daily delivery of coffee. Photo courtesy of the respondents

The first time she brought coffee, Echo recalled, she couldn't help being quiet as soon as she was near the hospital. Ambulances were coming and going, armed medics were on standby, and a 200-meter road would take two or three minutes. "every time I went in, I was very well behaved, like a soldier hearing a military song. That scene had a huge impact on us. "

Coffee is generally placed in the canteen entrance of the Logistics Department, where the concentration of lunch boxes, fruits and other materials placed. Put Down the coffee, the hospital volunteers armed to come out, waiting for them to be separated from a certain distance before the coffee truck away, sent to the hospital and other places.

On the third day, the volunteers saw that they were bringing coffee again. One of them, an older woman with red eyes, suddenly bowed and thanked them.

Then Xiao Hao followed Echo to deliver coffee, just in time for five or six paramedics to pick it up. After the coffee was handed over, "All of a sudden five or six of them bowed to us, and we were a little overwhelmed, and we bowed to them and told them to take care of themselves. It was the first time in my life that I've ever seen that and I'll never forget it. "

Each Coffee Cup sent to the Medical Staff Has Tian Yazhen's handwritten blessing, "the doctor is the most handsome" , "the nurse is the most beautiful" , "thanks for having you" , "go to Wuhan" , have this custom-made cup of coffee with the temperature of each Barista's hand. Sometimes people will buy some juice, chocolate with coffee to send. The medics would occasionally give them half a keg of alcohol.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Volunteers deliver coffee to inpatient departments and other places for distribution. Photo courtesy of the respondents

Unable to communicate face-to-face, many medical staff will be in the business backstage message. "The first time I drank your coffee was when I finished the seven-and-a-half-hour day shift in my protective suit. I didn't drink water or go to the toilet since 8:00 in the morning. The first thing I did when I got back to the department was to see a lot of coffee on the dining table and immediately open it and finish it. " "In order to take care of the medical staff who don't drink coffee, you were kind enough to pair it with fruit juice. " Tian Yazhen said, these responses are their greatest encouragement.

As the epidemic continued to spread, we learned that many hospital staff were also infected, some have no beds, or even can not go home self-isolation, can only stay in the hospital, the heart is very sad. Tian Yazhen made a decision to change the name of the "Chinese Latte" they sent every day. They didn't want to be sentimental. "Wuhan Angel" and "Wuhan Hero" were all too Corny, so they simply changed the name to "Wuhan Latte" , this is the coffee of the Wuhan People. "We commemorate these days with the most precious thing in the shop. "

"Even if one day the shop collapsed, can not go on, that last cup of coffee must also be sent to the hands of the medical staff, " Tian Yazhen said.

"Cloud Coffee" from all over the country

On Feb. 9, the 15th day after Wakanda's coffee delivery, an article in the coffee vertical press account brought the low key cafe to the public, where it was quickly republished and read more than 100,000 times overnight.

Some said it was "the help of ordinary people" , others said they were "the guardians of the city" , and many netizens said "after the epidemic is over, we must go to Wakanda and punch in. "

But others say they're hyping it.

Busy Making Coffee Tian Yazhen and friends do not know they have become the focus of public opinion.

The next day, have coffee beans, milk suppliers call, said to donate, Tian Yazhen declined temporarily, said the store is still adequate supplies, and Wuhan is not convenient logistics. They used to scavenge fresh milk for the day, first thing in the morning when a fresh supermarket opened. The coffee shop's milk suppliers donated milk and fresh milk when they learned they were making pro bono coffee, and the docking coffee bean suppliers also sponsored 50 kilograms of Colombian coffee beans.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Sina, the Iranian Barista, is not a big Talker, but he does his best with every cup of coffee he has. Photo courtesy of the respondents

On the morning of February 11, Tian Yazhen found that people kept transferring money through wechat and alipay. "I sent them back, and then I sent them back. " On the Popular Review Site, a sum of money suddenly appeared, and she wondered where it came from, later, it was discovered that the payment was made through the "pay bill" function on Yelp, most of which were 20,30,50 yuan, 500,1,000 yuan, from all over the country, and even from the coffee industry in Taiwan. Orders are piling up in the background, and voice mail is growing by the hundreds.

Originally, the netizen initiated an online check-up donation, hoping to order a cup of hot coffee for the doctor and nurse. By the Netizen Call"cloud coffee"be born thus.

By the evening of February 15, the store had received 13,571 orders, totaling more than 1.63 million yuan for Wakanda coffee. Faced with such a staggering number, everyone was pleasantly surprised and moved. "Your heart is racing, and behind you there's like a one hundred thousand people standing behind you, " Echo said of how she felt.

Before this, Tian Yazhen never thought to be able to do which day. I'm just GONNA keep doing it until I run out of supplies at all seven stores. But now see so many people say "do not want so warm coffee shop closed" , they decided to do their best to adhere to the wishes of the majority of Internet users, "cloud coffee" to the hands of each medical staff.

The store now records donations received on a daily basis. "The post-yelp statistics are so powerful and transparent that all order numbers can be found, " Tian said. Aside from the cost of raw materials, the rest of the money will be used to make coffee until the day the epidemic ends. All the remaining money, they will find the most reliable foundation, set up the Wuhan Medical Staff Exclusive Fund, Wuhan Latte Fund, all donated to the fight against the epidemic in Wuhan, the first line of medical staff, along with a list of all the people who have donated.

"So grateful to have such a warm-blooded, kind-hearted group of friends. "

On February 17, two days after a heavy snowfall in Wuhan, the streets were still empty with low temperatures. After contact, Shandong Medical Rescue Team medical staff also received a "Wuhan Latte" from Wakanda, hot, holding in his hands, like a return to an ordinary day. A doctor, holding a cup of coffee, took a Selfie in a hotel and wrote in a friend's circle: On the day of victory, be sure to go to the hotel for a drink.

Now that Wakanda's free coffee service has spread to three nearby hospitals, some medical teams in Wuhan have contacted them to deliver coffee. Each Cup of coffee, in addition to the blessing, but also will write the donation of the user ID name.

Do Not hide the home coffee staff can not hide, Tian Yazhen parents first time call let her must pay attention to protection, protect themselves. The family knew that what her daughter had decided to do could not be dissuaded.

Sina's stay in Wuhan to make coffee has become even more popular in Iran. The Chinese Ambassador to Iran, Chang Hua, praised Sina on social media. Sina's parents didn't know the truth until they saw the news. They were also moved by his actions. "A lot of people in my home city went to tell my mother that they saw what I did in China on the news, and they were very proud of me. "

Sina has been in Wuhan for two years, and he says he has never seen Wuhan like this. On the night of February 7, as he sat in his room, he heard "anyone" outside his window, "anyone else? " And "yes" coming from another building. Then they started shouting, "Go Wuhan, Go Wuhan, Go Wuhan. " Among them was the voice of a child, who was about to burst into tears, "I was shocked at that moment. There was a special emotion in those voices. They were so moving and beautiful. It was one of the best experiences of my life. I will always remember that night. "

Like many people in Wuhan, people are praying that the epidemic will end soon.

Xiao Hao, a native of Wuhan, said he was determined to eat a bowl of premature hot and dry noodles on the day the epidemic ended.

Sina said he was going to have a good rest when the epidemic was over and start a long journey if he saved enough money.

Tian Yazhen did not seriously think of the end of the epidemic will do, just want to do a good job every day, the "Wuhan Latte" to more hospitals to go. She loves her friends more now than ever. "I am so grateful to have such a warm-blooded and kind-hearted group of friends. "

In her latest coffee diary, she writes: Every day on the way to the hospital to deliver coffee, we see farmers pulling their own vegetables directly to the medical team, the owner of a small restaurant delivering hundreds of meals to the medical staff, people travelling abroad carry boxes of face masks directly back to the hands of medical staff, we have seen a lot of anti-epidemic period of "retrograde. ". We did what we were supposed to do. We're just a Chinese person.
